# Shape Logo Maker

## Description
This is a Node.js command-line application I built that generates a simple SVG logo. You can customize the logo by choosing the text, text color, shape (circle, triangle, square), and shape color. The generated logo will be saved as an SVG file, perfect for use in web projects.

## Installation
To get started with the project, follow these steps:

1. Clone the repository:
   ```bash
   git clone <repo-url>
\
Navigate to the project directory:

bash
Copy code
cd ShapeLogoMaker
Install the dependencies:

bash
Copy code
npm install
Usage
Hereâ€™s how to generate your logo:

Run the application:

bash
Copy code
node index.js
Follow the prompts:

Enter up to 3 characters for the logo text.
Provide a text color (keyword or hex code).
Choose a shape (Circle, Triangle, or Square).
Provide a shape color (keyword or hex code).
After completing the prompts, the logo.svg file will be created in the project directory.

Open the logo.svg file in your browser or an SVG viewer to see your generated logo.

Tests
To ensure everything is working as expected, you can run the Jest tests for the shapes:

bash
Copy code
npm test
